	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">National Security Agency</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="National_Security_Agency#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="National_Security_Agency#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">U.S. signals intelligence organization</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"NSA" redirects here. It is not to be confused with <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA" title="NASA">NASA</a> or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Security_Council" title="National Security Council">National Security Council</a>.  For other uses, see <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NSA_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="NSA (disambiguation)">NSA (disambiguation)</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Security_Agency_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="National Security Agency (disambiguation)">National Security Agency (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
